javax.jaxtx.compensation
Interface Status

public interface Status

This enumeration class represents the states that a compensation transaction and participants may be in.

Version:
1.0 $Id: Status.java,v 1.1 2004/06/22 10:07:59 nmcl Exp $

Field Summary
static int ACTIVE
          The transaction or participant is in an active state.
static int CANCELED
          The transaction/participant has canceled successfully.
static int CANCELING
          The transaction/participant is in the process of canceling.
static int COMPENSATED
          The transaction/participant has compensated successfully for work performed.
static int COMPENSATING
          The transaction/participant is in the process of compensating for work performed.
static int COMPENSATION_FAILED
          The transaction/participant was asked to compensate, but compensation failed.
static int COMPLETED
          The transaction/participant has completed successfully.
static int COMPLETING
          The transaction/participant is in the process of completing.
static int COMPLETION_FAILED
          The transaction/participant was asked to complete, but this was not possible.
static int UNDO_ONLY
          The only possible outcome of the transaction/participant is for it to cancel or compensate.
 

Field Detail

ACTIVE

public static final int ACTIVE
The transaction or participant is in an active state. For the transaction this means that it has not started to terminate. In the case of a participant it may mean that the business service is still executing work or that it has not been told to terminate.

Constant Field Values

COMPLETING

public static final int COMPLETING
The transaction/participant is in the process of completing. This means that all work performed can be considered done and no further compensation information need be maintained.

See Also:

CANCELING

public static final int CANCELING
The transaction/participant is in the process of canceling. This means that all work performed can be considered undone and no further compensation information need be maintained.
